Oluwatosin Omojuyigbe The Kaduna State Government and the police have arraigned two suspects in connection with the gang-rape of an 18-year-old girl. PUNCH Metro had reported that the victim was allegedly raped on April 27, 2020, by five male friends in the Narayi community of the state. While two of the suspects were arrested, the others reportedly went into hiding. The families of the two arrested suspects had allegedly been mounting pressure on the victim’s family to drop the case and reportedly offered her mother N15,000 each as damages. The two suspects, Ezra Barnabas and Chiaguya Chigozie, were arraigned on Tuesday, on three counts of conspiracy, involuntary intoxication and rape before the Kaduna Magistrates’ Court 3. The suspects pleaded not guilty to the charges. The court ordered their remand in police custody and adjourned the case till June 10, 2020. Copyright PUNCH.
